]]'', 3 May 1954, p.8</ref><ref>Obituary in The Eagle, The Magazine of Bedford Modern School, Summer 1954, Vol. XXIX No.6, p.483</ref>\n* [[Ernest Clive Atkins|Colonel Ernest Clive Atkins]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Territorial Decoration|TD]] [[Deputy Lieutenant|DL]] [[Justice of the peace|JP]] (1870\u20131953), Commander of the 2/5th [[Royal Leicestershire Regiment|Leicestershire Regiment]], [[High Sheriff of Leicestershire]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/><ref>ATKINS OF HINCKLEY: 1722\u20131972 by J.S. Atkins. Atkins, Ltd. [[Hinckley]], 1972.  Page 40</ref>\n* [[Robert Leycester Haymes|Lieutenant-Colonel Robert Haymes]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1870\u20131942), first to establish an [[Observation post|OP]] at the [[Battle of Neuve Chapelle]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" /> \n* [[Herbert William Jackson|Major-General Herbert William Jackson]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of the Star of India|CSI]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1872\u20131940), Officer of the [[British Indian Army]]<ref>H.E. Vipan, ''A Register of the Old Boys of the Bedford Modern School'' (Bedford, no date), p.64</ref>\n* [[George Godfrey Massy Wheeler|Major George Godfrey Massy Wheeler]] [[Victoria Cross|VC]] (1873\u20131915), was a recipient of the [[Victoria Cross]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.roll-of-honour.com/Bedfordshire/BedfordModernSchoolWW1Memorial.html|title=Roll of Honour \u2013 Bedfordshire \u2013 Bedford Modern School \u2013 World War 1|work=roll-of-honour.com|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Arthur Charles Rothery Nutt|Lieutenant-Colonel Arthur Charles Rothery Nutt]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1873\u20131946), inventor of the [[artillery miniature range]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Charles Foulkes (British Army officer)|Major-General Charles Howard Foulkes]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1875\u20131969), Britain's chief adviser on [[gas warfare]]<ref name=\"Who Was W