t Dickinson Oxland]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1889\u20131959), Group Commander in [[Bomber Command]] (1943\u201344)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Edye Rolleston Manning|Air Commodore Edye Rolleston Manning]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1889\u20131957), senior officer in the [[Royal Air Force]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=A1AfAQAAMAAJ&q=DSO+bedford+modern&dq=DSO+bedford+modern|title=The Aeroplane|accessdate=14 November 2015|year=1935}}</ref><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Air CDRE. E.J. Manning'', 29 April 1957, p.12</ref>\n* [[Charles Henry Elliott-Smith|Air Commodore Charles Henry Elliott-Smith]] [[Air Force Cross (United Kingdom)|AFC]] (1889\u20131994), senior officer in the [[Royal Air Force]]<ref name=\"autogenerated49\">{{cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/community/5183/?page=49 |title=Community: Bedford Modern School - List of Old Bedford Modernians serving in HM Forces 1914 - 1918. &#124; Lives of the First World War |publisher=Livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk |date= |accessdate=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n* [[H.D. Harvey-Kelly|Major H.D. Harvey-Kelly]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1891\u20131917), Squadron Commander, [[Royal Flying Corps]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" /><ref>The Eagle Vol. XIII no. 2 (July 1916), p. 24</ref>\n* [[John E. L. Hunter|Captain John Ellis Langford Hunter]] [[Distinguished Service Cross (United Kingdom)|DSC]] [[Distinguished Flying Cross (United Kingdom)|DFC]] (1897\u20131971), [[World War I]] [[flying ace]]<ref>''War Honours Won By Old Boys'', Bedford Modern School.  Published by H.W. Robinson, [[Bedford]], 1931</ref>\n* [[Robert Cecil Dawkins|Group Captain Robert Cecil Dawkins]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1903-1985), Station Commander at [[Tengah Air Base|RAF Tengah]] and [[Hendon Aerodrome|RAF Hendon]]<ref>''The Eagle'', The Magazine of [[Bedford Modern School]], Christmas 1951, Vol. XXVIII No.4</ref>\n* [[I. J. Fitch|Air Commodore I. J. Fitch]] (1903\u20131944), Deputy Director of Intelligence at the [[Air Ministry]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\" /><ref>>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', 5 September 1944</ref>\n* [[Ernest Leslie 'Johnny' Hyde|Wing Commander Ernest Leslie 'Johnny' Hyde]] [[Distinguished Flying Cross (United Kingdom)|DFC]] (1914\u20131942), senior officer in the [[Royal Air Force]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.ww2awards.com/person/46312|title=World War 2 Awards.com \u2013 HYDE, Ernest Leslie|work=ww2awards.com|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Roland Lee Knight|Squadron Leader Roland Anthony 'Tony' Lee Knight]] [[Distinguished Flying Cross (United Kingdom)|DFC]] (1917\u20131941), [[World War II]] [[flying ace]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.roll-of-honour.com/Bedfordshire/BedfordModernSchoolWW2Memorial.html|title=Roll of Honour \u2013 Bedfordshire \u2013 Bedford Modern School \u2013 World War 2|work=roll-of-honour.com|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Army===\n* [[Francis John Fowler|Major-General Francis John Fowler]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1864\u20131939) Commander of the [[Derajat Brigade]] (1914\u201316)<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n* [[Charles Astley Fowler|Major-General Charles Astley Fowler]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of the Star of India|CSI]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1865\u20131940), Brigade Commander at the [[Battle of Loos]], 1915<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n* [[Arthur Long (Brigadier-General)|Brigadier-General Sir Arthur Long]] [[Order of the British Empire|KBE]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1866\u20131941), Director of Transport and Supplies, Macedonia and The Black Sea<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Reginald Ruston|Colonel Reginald Ruston]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] (1867\u20131963), commander of the [[Mounted infantry]] of the [[Devonshire Regiment|Devon Regiment]] (1891\u20131903)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Robert Townshend Anwyl-Passingham|Major R.T. Anwyl-Passingham]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Deputy Lieutenant|DL]] [[Justice of the peace|JP]] (1867\u20131926), Commander of the [[72nd Punjabis]], [[High sheriff|High Sheriff]] of [[Merionethshire]]<ref>Register of the Old Boys of the [[Bedford Modern School]]. Compiled by H.E. Vipan. Published in [[Bedford]] by W. Robinson, 1900. Chapter IV, School Honours, p. vii</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thegazette.co.uk/London/issue/33030/page/1874|title=Page 1874 &#124; Issue 33030, 17 March 1925 &#124; London Gazette &#124; The Gazette}}</ref>\n* [[Gerald Robert Poole|Lieutenant-General Gerald Robert Poole]] [[Companion of The Most Honourable Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Companion of the Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1868\u20131937), Commandant of the [[Royal Marine Artillery]]<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n* [[Charles Forbes Buchan|Lt.Col Charles Forbes Buchan]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Order of Saint John (chartered 1888)|OStJ]] (1869-1954), Deputy Assistant Director at the [[War Office]] during [[World War I|WW1]]<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', 3 May 1954, p.8</ref><ref>Obituary in The Eagle, The Magazine of Bedford Modern School, Summer 1954, Vol. XXIX No.6, p.483</ref>\n* [[Ernest Clive Atkins|Colonel Ernest Clive Atkins]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Territorial Decoration|TD]] [[Deputy Lieutenant|DL]] [[Justice of the peace|JP]] (1870\u20131953), Commander of the 2/5th [[Royal Leicestershire Regiment|Leicestershire Regiment]], [[High Sheriff of Leicestershire]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/><ref>ATKINS OF HINCKLEY: 1722\u20131972 by J.S. Atkins. Atkins, Ltd. [[Hinckley]], 1972.  Page 40</ref>\n* [[Robert Leycester Haymes|Lieutenant-Colonel Robert Haymes]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1870\u20131942), first to establish an [[Observation post|OP]] at the [[Battle of Neuve Chapelle]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" /> \n* [[Herbert William Jackson|Major-General Herbert William Jackson]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of the Star of India|CSI]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1872\u20131940), Officer of the [[British Indian Army]]<ref>H.E. Vipan, ''A Register of the Old Boys of the Bedford Modern School'' (Bedford, no date), p.64</ref>\n* [[George Godfrey Massy Wheeler|Major George Godfrey Massy Wheeler]] [[Victoria Cross|VC]] (1873\u20131915), was a recipient of the [[Victoria Cross]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.roll-of-honour.com/Bedfordshire/BedfordModernSchoolWW1Memorial.html|title=Roll of Honour \u2013 Bedfordshire \u2013 Bedford Modern School \u2013 World War 1|work=roll-of-honour.com|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Arthur Charles Rothery Nutt|Lieutenant-Colonel Arthur Charles Rothery Nutt]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1873\u20131946), inventor of the [[artillery miniature range]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Charles Foulkes (British Army officer)|Major-General Charles Howard Foulkes]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1875\u20131969), Britain's chief adviser on [[gas warfare]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Herbert Cecil Potter|Brigadier-General Herbert Cecil Potter]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1875\u20131964)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Charles Temple Morris|Colonel Charles Temple Morris]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1876\u20131956), Commander of the 5th Battalion of the [[1st Punjab Regiment]] between 1921 and 1926<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mocavo.com/Whos-Who-Men-and-Women-of-the-Time-1935/107381/2979#2436|title=Whos Who, Men and Women of the Time, 1935|work=Mocavo|accessdate=27 May 2015}}</ref>\n* [[James Meldrum Knox|Lieutenant-Colonel James Knox]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO&bar]] (1878\u20131918), Battalion Commander, [[Royal Warwickshire Regiment]], 1915\u201318<ref>H.E. Vipan, ''A Register of the Old Boys of the Bedford Modern School''(Bedford, no date), p. 72</ref><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Lieutenant-Colonel J.M. Knox D.S.O., Royal Warwick Regiment'', 3 October 1918, p.3</ref>\n* [[Herbert Thomas Dobbin|Brigadier-General Herbert Dobbin]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1878\u20131946), [[Colonel-Commandant]], [[Iraq Levies]], the [[Duke of Cornwall's Light Infantry]]<ref>''Who was Who Vol. IV, 1941\u201350'' (London, 1980), p. 319.</ref>\n* [[Arthur Turner (British Army officer)|Brigadier-General Arthur Turner]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1878\u20131952), [[Cricket]]er, [[rugby union]] player and soldier<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/england/content/player/21615.html|title=Arthur Turner|work=Cricinfo|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Wilfrid Stanley Richmond|Colonel Wilfrid Stanley Richmond]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Institution of Civil Engineers|MICE]] (1881\u20131962), Deputy Director of Roads in the [[British Expeditionary Force (World War I)|BEF]] during [[World War I]]<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Colonel W.S. Richmond'', 30 January 1962, p.15</ref><ref>War Honours Won By Old Boys, Bedford Modern School. Published by H.W. Robinson, [[Bedford]], 1931</ref>\n* [[Henry Cecil Prescott|Lieutenant-Colonel Henry Cecil Prescott]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] (1882\u20131960), Inspector of Police in [[Iraq]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Guy Sutton Bocquet|Colonel Guy Sutton Bocquet]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] [[Volunteer Officers' Decoration|VD]] [[Royal Society of Arts|FRSA]] (1882\u20131961), [[Aide-de-camp|ADC]] to the [[Governor-General of India|Viceroy of India]]<ref>School of the Black and Red, A.G. Underwood (2010 edition). Hardback p.288: ''President of the OBM Club'' in 1952</ref><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Mr. Guy Bocquet'', 21 January 1961, p.8</ref>\n* [[Brigadier Harold Evelyn William Bell Kingsley]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1885\u20131970), Aide-de-Camp to King [[George VI]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\">''Who Was Who'', Published by A&C Black</ref>\n* [[Charles Hamilton Grant Hume Harvey-Kelly|Lieut-Col Charles HGH Harvey-Kelly]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1885\u20131982), Military Attache in [[Kabul]] (1924-6)<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\" />\n* [[Lieutenant-General Reginald Dawson Hopcraft Lough]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1886\u20131958), [[Aide-de-camp]] to King [[George VI]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\" />\n* [[Arthur Edward Flynn Fawcus|Lt.-Col. A.E.F. Fawcus]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] [[Military Cross|MC]] [[Territorial Decoration|TD]] (1886\u20131936), Commander, 1/5th [[Staffordshire Rangers|North Staffordshire Regiment]], 1/5th [[Sherwood Foresters]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" /><ref>War Honours Won By Old Boys, Bedford Modern School, Published by H.W. Robinson, [[Bedford]], 1931</ref>\n* [[George Croxton Walker (military officer)|Major George Croxton Walker]] (1888\u20131936) [[Officer of the Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Military Cross|MC]] [[Territorial Decoration|TD]], distinguished himself in [[World War I]]<ref>Obituary in ''[[Times & Citizen|The Bedford Times]]'', ''Major G. C. Walker'', ''Death of a Distinguished Military Officer'', 31 July 1936</ref><ref name=\"autogenerated17\">{{cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/community/5183/?page=17 |title=Community: Bedford Modern School - List of Old Bedford Modernians serving in HM Forces 1914 - 1918. &#124; Lives of the First World War |publisher=Livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk |date= |accessdate=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n* [[Wynn Bagnall|Captain Wynn Bagnall]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1890\u20131931), [[Canadian Field Artillery]], model for a statue by [[James Earle Fraser (sculptor)|James Fraser]] in [[Winnipeg, Manitoba]]<ref>''The Eagle'' Vol. XII no. 9 (December 2015),p. 338</ref>\n* [[Melville Rysdale Ten Broeke|Lieutenant-Colonel Melville Ten Broeke]] [[Military Cross|MC&bar]] (1891\u20131963), commander of [[Princess Patricia's Canadian Light Infantry|Princess Patricia's Canadian Light Infantry Regiment]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=je2Jz_1c21sC&pg=PA719&lpg=PA719&dq=ten+broeke+vancouver+imperial#v=onepage&q=ten%20broeke%20vancouver%20imperial|title=Imperial Vancouver Island|accessdate=13 March 2015|isbn=9781450059633|last1=Bosher|first1=J. F.|date=April 2010}}</ref>\n* [[Leonard Arthur Hawes|Major-General L.A. Hawes]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] [[Military Cross|MC]] [[Deputy Lieutenant|DL]] (1892\u20131986), Commanded the transport to France of the [[British Expeditionary Force (World War II)|BEF]] during [[World War I]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[W.C.V. Galwey|Brigadier W.C.V. Galwey]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Military Cross|MC&bar]] (1897\u20131977), senior officer who served in [[World War I]] and [[World War II]]<ref name=\"Burke's Irish Family Records\" >Hugh Montgomery-Massingberd, ''Burke's Irish Family Records'' London, U.K.: Burkes Peerage Ltd, 1976</ref>\n* [[Ernest Dynes|Brigadier Ernest Dynes]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1903\u20131968) was [[Aide-de-camp]] to HM Queen [[Elizabeth II]] (1955\u201357)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Thomas Henry Scott Galletly|Brigadier Thomas Henry Scott Galletly]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO&bar]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1905\u20131972), Commander of the 1st Brigade, [[Arab League]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\" />\n* [[Major-General Reginald Booth Stockdale]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1908\u20131979) Colonel Commandant, [[REME]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\" />\n* [[Peter Boughey|Lt.-Col. Edward Peter Fletcher Boughey]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1911\u20131986), [[Special Operations Executive]]<ref>Bedford Modern School. A.B.C. List. Easter Term 1923</ref>\n* [[Keith Burch|Major-General Keith Burch]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1931\u20132013)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n\n===Navy===\n* [[Willoughby Baynes Huddleston|Commander Willoughby Huddleston]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] (1866\u20131953), [[Aide-de-camp|ADC]] to [[John Sinclair, 1st Baron Pentland|Lord Pentland]], [[Governor of Madras]] (1912\u201319)<ref name=\"auto2\"/><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Captain W.B. Huddleston'', 5 May 1953, p.8</ref>\n* [[Thomas Oloff de Wet|Captain Thomas Oloff de Wet]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1869\u20131940), Principal Naval Transport Officer during the [[Occupation of Constantinople|evacuation of Constantinople]] in 1923<ref>A Register of the Old Boys of the [[Bedford Modern School]]. Compiled and Edited by H.E. Vipan.  Published in [[Bedford]] by W.J. Robinson, 1900.  School Honours; p. ix</ref>\n* [[Alfred Ransom (Royal Navy officer)|Rear Admiral Alfred Ransom]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1871\u20131953), senior officer in the Royal Navy<ref>H.E. Vipan,''A Register of the Old Boys of the Bedford Modern School'' (Bedford, no date), p. 103</ref>\n* [[Sir Ernest Whiteside Huddleston]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Royal Indian Navy|RIN]] (1874\u20131959), [[Aide-de-camp]] to the [[Governor-General of India|Viceroy of India]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\" />\n* [[Francis Walter Despard Twigg|Captain Francis Walter Despard Twigg]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1883-1951), senior officer in the Royal Navy<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/community/5183/?page=13|title=Community: Bedford Modern School - List of Old Bedford Modernians serving in HM Forces 1914 - 1918. &#124; Lives of the First World War|website=livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk}}</ref>\n* [[Herbert Roff Newton|Commander Herbert Newton]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Deputy Lieutenant|DL]] (1900\u20131973), [[Royal Navy]] Commander and [[Deputy Lieutenant]] of [[Bedfordshire]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\" />\n* [[Rear-Admiral Jack Kenneth Highton]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1904\u20131988), [[Aide-de-camp]] to Queen [[Elizabeth II]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Fred Stovin-Bradford|Captain Frederick Stovin-Bradford]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Distinguished Service Cross (United Kingdom)|DSC&Bar]] (1919\u20131974), [[Royal Navy]] Commander ([[Fleet Air Arm]])<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\" />\n* [[Sir Ted Horlick|Vice-Admiral Sir Ted Horlick]] [[Order of the British Empire|KBE]] (born 1925), Director General of British Ships (1979\u201383), Chief Naval Engineer Officer (1981\u201383)<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\" />\n\n==Industry and commerce==\n[[File:John Howard (1791\u20131878), Mayor of Bedford.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[John Howard (industrialist)|John Howard]]]]\n[[File:Arthur John Carter - Queensland Politician.png|thumb|115px|right|[[Arthur Carter (Queensland politician)|Arthur Carter]]]]\n[[File:George Herbert Farrar01a.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[George Farrar|Sir George Farrar Bt]]]]\n* [[John Howard (Industrialist)|John Howard]] (1791\u20131878), [[Business magnate|industrialist]], inventor of agricultural equipment and four times [[Mayor of Bedford]]<ref name=\"worldcat.org1\">{{Cite book|title=The Harpur Trust, 1552\u20131973.|work=worldcat.org|isbn=9780950291703|year=1973|oclc = 903515}}</ref>\n* [[James Howard (agriculturalist)|James Howard]] (1821\u20131889), industrialist and inventor of agricultural equipment. [[Member of Parliament|MP]] for Bedford<ref name=\"worldcat.org1\"/>\n* [[Frederick Howard (industrialist)|Sir Frederick Howard]] [[Justice of the peace|JP]] [[Deputy Lieutenant|DL]] (1828\u20131915), [[Business magnate|industrialist]]<ref name=\"worldcat.org1\"/>\n* [[Charles Wells (brewer)|Captain Charles Wells]] (1842\u20131914), founder of [[Charles Wells Ltd]], [[progenitor]] of the [[Wells baronets]] of [[Felmersham]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://virtual-library.culturalservices.net/webingres/bedfordshire/vlib/0.digitised_resources/bedford_digitisation_charles_wells_brewery.htm|title=charles wells brewery timeline \u2013 Digitised Resources \u2013 The Virtual Library|author=Bedford Borough Council and Central Bedfordshire Council|work=culturalservices.net|accessdate=1 March 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Arthur Carter (Queensland politician)|Hon. Arthur Carter]] (1847\u20131917), businessman, Australian [[Consul (representative)|Consul]] to [[Norway]], [[Members of the Queensland Legislative Council|Member of the Queensland Legislative Council]]<ref>{{Cite book|chapter-url=http://adb.anu.edu.au/biography/carter-arthur-john-5521|title=Biography \u2013 Arthur John Carter \u2013 Australian Dictionary of Biography|work=anu.edu.au|accessdate=30 January 2015|chapter=Carter, Arthur John (1847\u20131917)|publisher=National Centre of Biography, Australian National University}}</ref><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''The Hon. A. J. Carter'', 10 November 1917, p.3</ref>\n* [[Sir George Farrar, 1st Baronet]] (1859\u20131915), mining magnate, politician and soldier<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oxfordindex.oup.com/view/10.1093/oi/authority.20110803095811125|title=Sir George Herbert Farrar|work=oup.com|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bodley.ox.ac.uk/dept/scwmss/wmss/online/blcas/farrar-george.html|title=Papers of Sir George Farrar and family|work=ox.ac.uk|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Henry Batten Huddleston|Lt. Col. Henry Batten Huddleston]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Volunteer Officers' Decoration|VD]] (1864\u20131944), Chief Agent and later a Director of the Burma Railways<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/community/5183/?page=12|title=Community: Bedford Modern School - List of Old Bedford Modernians serving in HM Forces 1914 - 1918. &#124; Lives of the First World War|website=livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk}}</ref>\n* [[Walter Nutt (businessman)|Hon. Walter Nutt]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1874\u20131940), managing director of [[Straits Trading Company|The Straits Trading Company]] (1918\u201321)<ref>1891 England Census, Boarder at Bedford Modern School</ref>\n* [[Noel Mobbs|Sir Noel Mobbs]] [[Royal Victorian Order|KCVO]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1878\u20131959), founder of [[Slough Estates]] and [[High sheriff]] of [[Buckinghamshire]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[E.E. Blake]] (1879\u20131961), Chairman of [[Eastman Kodak|Kodak UK]]<ref name=\"mocavo.co.uk\"/>\n* [[William Alfred Pickwoad|William Pickwoad]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Royal Society of Arts|FRSA]] (1886\u20131975), prominent in South America's railway industry. Founding director of the [[Central Bank of Bolivia]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/> \n* [[W. T. Godber]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1904\u20131981), authority on agriculture and [[agricultural engineering]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Mr W.T. Godber'', 24 April 1981, p.14</ref>\n* [[Sir Henry Cecil Johnson]] [[Order of the British Empire|KBE]] (1906\u20131988), chairman of the [[British Railways Board]] (1968\u201371)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Alastair George MacKenzie]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1915\u20131989), prominent figure in [[Southeast Asia|South East Asian]] insurance during the 1960s and 1970s<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=kn4uAQAAIAAJ&q=alastair+george+mackenzie+bedford+modern&dq=alastair+george+mackenzie+bedford+modern|title=Who's who in Malaysia and Guide to Singapore|accessdate=14 November 2015|year=1967}}</ref>\n* [[Francis Coulson]] [[Order of the British Empire|MBE]] (1919\u20131998), [