 1961), author, historian and journalist specialising in [[Black British]] history and literature<ref>{{cite web|url=http://literature.britishcouncil.org/s-i-martin|title=S. I. Martin \u2013 British Council Literature|author=British Council|work=britishcouncil.org|accessdate=28 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.academia.edu/7333251|title=S.I. Martin, April 24, 1961\u2013 |author=Leila Kamali|journal=Academia.edu|accessdate=28 May 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Stephen May (novelist)|Stephen May]] (born 1964), novelist, playwright and TV writer<ref>Eagle News, Vol 5 No 4 (Issue 105) May 2012, p.115</ref>\n* [[Toby Litt]] (born 1968), author (''[[Beatniks (novel)|Beatniks]]'', ''[[Corpsing (novel)|Corpsing]]'', ''[[Finding Myself]]'')<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n\n==Medicine==\n[[File:George Cleghorn (1850-1902).JPG|thumb|115px|right|[[George Cleghorn]]]]\n[[File:Walter Jessop.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[Walter Jessop (surgeon)|Walter Jessop FRCS]]]]\n* [[George Cleghorn]] (1850\u20131902), President of the [[New Zealand Medical Association]]<ref>Obituary notice: George Cleghorn M.D. ''The Eagle'', vol. viii, no. 8, July 1903, pp. 338\u201339</ref>\n* [[Walter Jessop (surgeon)|Walter Jessop]] [[Royal College of Surgeons|FRCS]] (1853\u20131917), [[Ophthalmology|Ophthalmic Surgeon]] at [[St Bartholomew's Hospital|St Bartholomew's]], President of the UK Ophthalmological Society<ref>{{cite web|url=http://livesonline.rcseng.ac.uk/biogs/E002362b.htm|title=Jessop, Walter Hamilton Hylton \u2013 Biographical entry \u2013 Plarr's Lives of the Fellows Online|work=rcseng.ac.uk|accessdate=29 January 2015}}</ref><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Mr. W.H. Jessop'', 19 February 1917, p.12</ref>\n* [[Major-General Harold Percy Waller Barrow]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1856\u20131957), Honorary Surgeon to King [[George V]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ramc-ww1.com/profile.php?cPath=211_655&profile_id=9982&osCsid=29|title=RAMC: Royal Army Medical Corps WW1|work=ramc-ww1.com|accessdate=29 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[George Harris (physician)|Major-General George Francis Angelo Harris]] [[Order of the Star of India|CSI]] [[Royal College of Physicians|FRCP]] (1856\u20131931), Professor at the Calcutta Medical School<ref>{{cite web|url=http://munksroll.rcplondon.ac.uk/Biography/Details/2048|title=Munks Roll Details for George Francis Angelo Harris|work=rcplondon.ac.uk|accessdate=29 January 2015}}</ref><ref>Obituary, ''Major-General Harris'', ''[[The Times]]'', 18 April 1931, p.12</ref>\n* [[Rickard William Lloyd]] [[Membership of the Royal College of Surgeons|MRCS]] LRCPEd (1859\u20131933), Consulting [[Anesthesiologist|Anaesthetist]] and author<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1136/bmj.1.3777.940-b |pmc=2368701 |title=Dr. Rickard William Lloyd |journal=BMJ |volume=1 |issue=3777 |pages=940 |year=1933 |pmid=20777569}}</ref>\n* [[Charles Hubert Roberts]] [[Royal College of Surgeons|FRCS]] [[Royal College of Physicians|FRCP]] (1865\u20131929), Obstetrician and Gynaecologist<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.munksroll.rcplondon.ac.uk/Biography/Details/3791 |title=Munk's Roll Vol. IV (1826\u20131925), Charles Hubert Roberts, retrieved March, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151017022809/http://munksroll.rcplondon.ac.uk/Biography/Details/3791 |archivedate=17 October 2015 }}</ref><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Dr. C.H. Roberts'', 2 February 1929, p.14</ref>\n* [[Claud Worth|Claud Alley Worth]] [[Fellowship of the Royal College of Surgeons|FRCS]] (1869\u20131936), ophthalmologist, inventor of the [[Worth 4 dot test]] and [[Haploscope|Worth's Ambyloscope]], world authority on [[Strabismus|squint]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Frank Atcherley Rose]] [[Fellowship of the Royal College of Surgeons|FRCS]] (1873\u20131935), surgeon at [[St Bartholomew's Hospital]] (1928\u201331)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://livesonline.rcseng.ac.uk/biogs/E004534b.htm|title=Rose, Frank Atcherley \u2013 Biographical entry \u2013 Plarr's Lives of the Fellows Online|work=rcseng.ac.uk|accessdate=29 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Thomas Shephard Novis]] [[Royal College of Surgeons|FRCS]] (1874\u20131962), Professor of Surgery at [[Grant Medical College]], [[Bombay]]<ref>''The Eagle'' Vol. XVI, no. 1 (March 1926), p. 59</ref>\n* [[Major-General Harrold Rothery Nutt|Major-General Harold Rothery Nutt]] [[Fellow of the Royal College of Surgeons|FRCS]] (1876\u20131953), Honorary Surgeon to the [[Governor-General of India|Viceroy of India]] and King [[George V]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://livesonline.rcseng.ac.uk/biogs/E005200b.htm|title=Nutt, Harold Rothery \u2013 Biographical entry \u2013 Plarr's Lives of the Fellows Online|work=rcseng.ac.uk|accessdate=29 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Cyril Arthur Bennett Horsford]] [[Fellowship of the Royal College of Surgeons|FRCS]] (1876\u20131953), [[Laryngologist]] to the [[Royal College of Music]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://livesonline.rcseng.ac.uk/biogs/E005060b.htm|title=Horsford, Cyril Arthur Bennett \u2013 Biographical entry \u2013 Plarr's Lives of the Fellows Online|work=rcseng.ac.uk|accessdate=29 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[John Wycliffe Linnell]] [[Royal College of Physicians|FRCP]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1878\u20131967), Consulting Physician<ref>{{cite web|url=http://munksroll.rcplondon.ac.uk/Biography/Details/2757|title=Munks Roll Details for John Wycliffe Linnell|work=rcplondon.ac.uk|accessdate=29 January 2015}}</ref><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Dr. John Wycliffe Linnell MC FRCP'', 12 December 1967, p.12</ref>\n* [[Henry Howarth Bashford|Sir Henry Howarth Bashford]] (1880\u20131961), Honorary Physician to King [[George VI]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://munksroll.rcplondon.ac.uk/Biography/Details/279|title=Munks Roll Details for Henry Howarth (Sir) Bashford|work=rcplondon.ac.uk|accessdate=29 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Adolphe Abrahams|Sir Adolphe Abrahams]] [[Orde