orian Order|KCVO]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1883\u20131951). Financial Secretary to three Kings (1935\u201337)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Davenport Fabian Cartwright Blunt]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] (1888\u20131965), [[Undersecretary|Under-Secretary]] at [[HM Treasury]] (1946\u201348)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Reginald Berkeley]] (1890\u20131935), [[Liberal Party (UK)|Liberal]] [[Member of parliament|MP]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Sir Laurence George Gale]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1905\u20131969). Controller, Royal Ordnance Factories<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Hugh Chaplin]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] (1905\u20131996), Principal Keeper of Printed Books at the [[British Museum]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/incoming/obituary-a-h-chaplin-5586653.html|title=obituary: A. H. Chaplin|date=4 January 1997|website=The Independent}}</ref>\n* [[John Percival Morton|Jack Morton]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1911\u20131985). Assistant Undersecretary of State at the [[Ministry of Defence (United Kingdom)|Ministry of Defence]] (1968\u201371)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Mr Jack Morton'', 13 June 1985, p.12</ref>\n* [[Philip Lionel Burton]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1914\u20131996), Head of the Civil Service Pay Research Unit between 1963 and 1971<ref>The Harpur Trust, 1552\u20131973, by Joyce Godber, 1973</ref>\n* [[Arthur Jones (Conservative politician)|Arthur Jones]] (1915\u20131991), [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] [[Member of parliament|MP]]. Mayor of Bedford<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Rowland Thomas Lovell Lee]] (1920\u20132005), [[Recorder (judge)|Recorder]] of the [[Crown Court]] (1979\u201392)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Edgar William Boyles]] (1921\u20132001), [[Undersecretary|Under-Secretary]] at the [[Inland Revenue]] (1975\u201381)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Tony Hart (politician)|Tony Hart]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1923\u20132009), leader of [[Kent County Council|Kent C.C.]] during the development of the [[Channel Tunnel]], [[Eurostar]] and the [[Dartford Crossing|Dartford Bridge]]<ref>{{Cite newspaper|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/politics-obituaries/5819641/Tony-Hart.html|title=Tony Hart|date=13 July 2009|work=Telegraph.co.uk|accessdate=13 June 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Brian Ernest Maitland Prophet]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Territorial Decoration|TD]] [[Deputy Lieutenant|DL]] (1928\u20132004), [[Deputy Lieutenant]] of [[Bedfordshire]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Sir Stanley John Odell]] (born 1929), former Chairman of the National Union of Conservative Constituency Associations<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n* [[Keith Speed|Sir Keith Speed]] [[Deputy Lieutenant|DL]] (1934-2018), [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] [[Member of parliament|MP]]. Undersecretary of State for Defence (1979\u201381)<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n* [[Jeffery John Mumford Speed]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Royal Society of Arts|FRSA]] [[Institute of Leadership and Management|FInstLM]] [[Royal Geographical Society|FRGS]] (born 1936) was Director of Fundraising at [[Conservative Campaign Headquarters|Conservative Central Office]]<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n* [[Jeffrey James West|Rev. Canon Jeffrey James West]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Royal Society of Arts|FRSA]] (born 1950), Inspector of Historic Buildings, [[English Heritage]] (1983\u201386)<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n* [[Patrick Hall (politician)|Patrick Hall]] (born 1951), [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] [[Member of parliament|MP]]<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n* [[Michael Crowther]] (born 1952), wildlife conservationist and founder of the [[Indianapolis Prize]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Nick Hawkins]], (born 1957), former [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] [[Member of parliament|MP]]<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n* [[Andrew Cha