ission for the Government of the [[Saar (League of Nations)|Saar Basin]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Herbert George Billson]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] (1871\u20131938), Chief Conservator of Indian Forests, 1922\u201326<ref>''Who was Who Vol. III, 1929\u20131940'' (London, 1967), p. 111</ref>\n* [[Sir William Pell Barton]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|KCIE]] (1871\u20131956). [[Resident (title)|Resident]] in [[Vadodara|Baroda]] (1919), [[Mysore]] (1920\u201325) and [[Hyderabad]] (1925\u201330)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Sir W. Barton'', 29 November 1956, p.15</ref>\n* [[William McKinnell]] (1873\u20131939), politician who served in the Legislative Assembly of [[Manitoba]], Canada (1920\u201336)<ref>''Pioneers and Prominent People of Manitoba'', Published by Canadian Publicity Co., 1925</ref>\n* [[Walter Nutt (businessman)|Hon. Walter Nutt]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1874\u20131940), a member of the [[Federated Malay States|Federal Malay States]] [[Legislative council]]<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=Yn25FY2pY3EC&pg=PA288&lpg=PA288&dq=walter+frederick+nutt#v=onepage&q=walter%20frederick%20nutt] Colonial Armies in Southeast Asia, edited by Karl Hack and Tobias Rettig.  First published by [[Routledge]], 2006</ref>\n* [[John Richard Donovan Glascott]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] (1877\u20131938), Chief Engineer of the [[Myanmar Railways|Burma Railways]], Member of the [[Legislative Council of Burma]]<ref>The Eagle, BMS Magazine, Vol.XXI No.6, July 1938</ref>\n* [[Sir Robert Daniel Richmond]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] (1878\u20131948), Chief Conservator, Indian Woods and Forests<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Sir Daniel Richmond'', May 5, 1948, p.7</ref>\n* [[Archie Rose]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] [[FRGS]] (1879\u20131961), diplomat, explorer and businessman in China<ref>H.E. Vipan, A Register of the Old Boys of the [[Bedford Modern School]], (Bedford, no date), p.107</ref>\n* [[Sir Francis Moncrieff Kerr-Jarrett]] (1885\u20131968), [[Custos Rotulorum]] of St James's, [[Jamaica]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Stanley Wyatt Smith]] (1887\u20131958), [[Consul (representative)|Consul-General]] of [[Manila]] (1938\u201342) and [[Honolulu]] (1943\u201344)<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Mr. S. Wyatt-Smith'', 19 November 1958, p.13</ref>\n* [[Ronald Okeden Alexander|Major-General Ronald Okeden Alexander]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1888\u20131949), Inspector General, Central Canada (1942\u201346)<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Charles George Hawes|Charles Hawes]] [[Companion of the Indian Empire|CIE]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1890\u20131963). Chief Engineer to the Government of [[Sind]]<ref>''Who was Who'' Vol. VI (1961\u201370) (London, 1972), p. 505</ref>\n* [[Frederick Williamson]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] (1891\u20131935), [[Consul (representative)|Consul-General]] of [[Kashgar]] (1927\u201330)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/><ref>Obituary in ''The Times'', ''Mr Frederick Williamson'', 19 November 1935, p.19</ref>\n* [[Reginald Philip Abigail]] (1892\u20131969), [[District Commissioner (British Colonial)|District Commissioner]] of [[Rakhine State|Arakan]] during the [[Japanese conquest of Burma|fall of Burma]] in 1942<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=PKIWAQAAIAAJ&dq=reginald+abigail+burma+kellys&q=abigail+bedford+modern|title=Kelly's Handbook to the Titled, Landed and Official Classes|accessdate=14 June 2015|year=1969|last1=Kelly's}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=oCUbAQAAIAAJ&dq=punjab+bedford+modern&q=abigail+bedford+modern|title=The India Office and Burma Office List|accessdate=14 June 2015|year=1947}}</ref>\n* [[Bertram St. Leger Ten Broeke]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1895\u20131962), Deputy Inspector-General of the Indian Police in [[Bihar]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/story/84029|title=Story: Bedford Modern School Eagle Magazine Obituary for B St L Ten-Broeke, CIE, MC died November 1962 &#124; Lives of the First World War|website=livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk}}</ref>\n* [[W. D. Harverson]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Royal School of Mines|ARSM]] [[Institute of Materials, Minerals and Mining|MIMM]] (1903\u201392), Commissioner of Mines in [[Kenya]] (1949\u201358) and [[Tanganyika]] (1958\u201362)<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=W11zAAAAMAAJ&dq=author+educated+bedford+modern&q=bedford+modern|title=An encyclopaedia of New Zealand|accessdate=6 June 2015|year=1966|last1=McLintock|first1=Alexander H.}}</ref>\n* [[Walter Ian James Wallace]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1905\u20131993), Assistant Undersecretary of State at the [[Colonial Office]] (1962\u201366)<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Arthur Mooring|Sir Arthur Mooring]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|KCMG]] (1908\u20131969), British [[Resident (title)|Resident]] in [[Zanzibar]] (1959\u20131963)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Cyril Herbert Williams]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1908\u20131983), Provincial Commissioner of the [[Nyanza Province]] of [[Kenya]] (1951\u201356)<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Roger Hawkins (politician)|Roger Tancred Robert Hawkins]] [[Legion of Merit (Rhodesia)|GLM]] [[Independence Commemorative Decoration|ICD]] (1915\u20131980), [[Rhodesia]]n politician and member of [[Ian Smith]]'s cabinet after [[Rhodesia]]'s [[Rhodesia's Unilateral Declaration of Independence|UDI]]<ref>Who's Who of Rhodesia, Mauritius, Central and East Africa: Supplement to the Who's Who of Southern Africa.  Combined Publishers, 1967</ref>\n* [[Victor Yarnell]] (1919\u20132005), American politician, [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] [[Mayor of Reading, Pennsylvania]] (1968\u20131972)<ref>http://www.house.state.pa.us/BMC/Bios/PDF/1603.PDF</ref>\n* [[Ian Arthur Naunton Cook|Colonel Ian Cook]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1934\u20131994), Commander of the [[Law enforcement in Vanuatu|Vanuatu Mobile Police Force]] (1980\u201384)<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Malcolm Geoffrey Hilson]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (born 1942), [[High Commissioner]] of [[Vanuatu]] (1997\u20132000)<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n* [[Paul Reddicliffe]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (born 1945), British Ambassador to the Kingdom of [[Cambodia]] (1994\u20131997)<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n\n==Religion==\n[[File:Bishops at Walsingham (4666974401) (Tony Robinson cropped).jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[Tony Robinson (bishop)|Tony Robinson]]]]\n* [[William Edward Toll|The Rt. Rev. William Toll]] (1843\u20131915), [[Suffragan bishop]] of the [[Episcopal Diocese of Chicago]] (1911\u201315)<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Thomas Blyth (cleric)|Canon Thomas Blyth]] [[Doctor of Divinity|DD]] (1844\u20131913), author and [[Commissary]] to the [[Anglican Diocese of Ottawa|Archbishop of Ottawa]] and [[Diocese of Niagara|Bishops of Niagara]]<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Canon T.A. Blyth'', 22 July 1913, p.11</ref>\n* [[Henry Arthur Lester|Rev. H.A. Lester]] [[Master of Arts (Oxbridge and Dublin)|MA]] (1873\u20131922), theologian, author and director of the [[Bishop of London|Bishop of London's]] Sunday School Council (1911\u20131922)<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''The Rev H. A. Lester'', 26 July 1922, p.16</ref><ref>{{Cite book |doi=10.1093/ww/9780199540884.013.U199273 |chapter=Lester, Rev. Henry Arthur, (died 24 July 1922), Director, Bishop of London's Sunday School Council |title=Who Was Who |year=2007 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldcat.org/search?q=au%3ALESTER%2C+Henry+Arthur.&dblist=638&fq=ap%3A%22lester%2C+henry+arthur%22&qt=facet_ap%3A|title=Results for 'au:LESTER, Henry Arthur.' > 'Henry Arthur Lester' [WorldCat.org]|publisher=}}</ref>\n* [[Thomas Hooton Micha